<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="572" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,389,1350]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,376,389,414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Generic Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is set apart from other New World 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1805" box="[908,1036,389,414]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pompilinae">Pompilinae</taxonomicName>
genera by a unique combination of characters: the lack of a distinct comb on the fore tarsus (two moderate spines the on basitarsus, none at the middle of the second joint) (
<figureCitation box="[383,463,461,486]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
); having the claws dentate in both sexes (
<figureCitation box="[931,1036,461,486]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Figs 1a,e</figureCitation>
); having a median longitudinal row of three setae on the underside of the apical tarsomere in the female (
<figureCitation box="[926,1007,497,522]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
); having only fine, curved setae at the tip of the metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[403,488,533,558]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
); having slender antennae (
<figureCitation box="[812,895,533,558]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
); having the basal vein ending just before the transverse vein in both sexes; having a moderately long marginal cell (
<figureCitation box="[958,1040,569,594]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
); having the anal vein ending near the fork of the cubitus in the hind wing; lacking a ventral metasomal brush in the male (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1241,605,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
); having a single pair of hooklets on the genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[525,608,641,666]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
); and apparently having the subgenital plate modified. This last character could not be observed because the subgenital plate had been destroyed in the process of extracting the genitalia by someone in the past.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="572" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,389,1350]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,440,749,774]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Generic Description</emphasis>
. Mandibles with two teeth on inner margin. Labrum without median slit, only slightly protruding from beneath clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[544,628,785,810]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[644,675,785,810]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">2b</figureCitation>
); clypeus with apical margin truncate (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1212,785,810]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1227,1259,785,810]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">2b</figureCitation>
), smoothly and broadly curved. Malar space very short (
<figureCitation box="[605,687,821,846]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[700,731,821,846]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">2b</figureCitation>
). Antennae elongate, segment three in both male and female at least 6 as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[418,499,857,882]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[512,541,858,882]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">2a</figureCitation>
). Pronotum rather short, without median impression (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1223,857,882]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1236,1265,858,882]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">2a</figureCitation>
). Postnotum as transverse band of variable width, not expanded on each side of the median line. Propodeum short with smooth contours laterally and with well-defined, slightly concave posterior declivity (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1119,929,954]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1133,1163,930,954]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">2a</figureCitation>
). Front tarsus of female without well-developed comb, internal face of front basitarsus with row of two thickened conical spines with apical spine 0.66 length of second tarsomere, and with second more posterior row of three shorter spines; apical tarsal segments spined beneath with median row of three spines in female; spines absent in male. Claws of female dentate (
<figureCitation box="[159,239,1073,1098]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
); claws of male dentate, except inner claw of front tarsus strongly curved and deeply cleft, apical segment of front tarsus of male weakly modified with inner lobe at apical sixth, only slightly veering from parallel. Pulvillus weakly developed, one-fifth length of claw, pulvillar comb moderately developed, of ~12 subparallel thickened rays (
<figureCitation box="[212,292,1181,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
). Fore wing with three SMCs (
<figureCitation box="[637,740,1181,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Figs 1a,c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[752,782,1182,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">2a</figureCitation>
); hind wing with anal vein arching up to meet median vein slightly before the cubital fork; anal lobe about 0.5 times length of submedian cell. Apical tergum of female with several backward-directed thin long setae, not differing from previous terga or apical sterna (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1279,1253,1278]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,520,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1428,519,1319]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neanoplius coeruleosomus female, holotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; C. fore wing; D. metasoma; and E. apical tarsomere of hind leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601566/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
). Male venter bare without secondary sexual characters such as tufts of setae; genitalia with basal hooklets single, aedeagus simple without spines or setae (
<figureCitation box="[504,586,1325,1350]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1314,580,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neanoplius coeruleosomus male, allotype. A. habitus; B. head, frontal view; and C. genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601568/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
